DOC.TEXT:
   Snow fell in Alaska early today, and fog covered much of the
South.
   The forecast called for sunshine for most of the country.
Florida looked for rain and snow was possible tonight in Idaho and
Montana.
   Highes in the 70s nad 80s were forecast from the Great Lakes to
the Mississippi Valley. Temperatures were expected to reach the 50s
in the Pacific Northwest, the 60s in the Northeast, the 70s in the
Midwest, the 80s in the Rockies and the 90s in the Southwest.
   The high temperature for the nation Monday was 95 degrees at
Gila Bend, Ariz.; Lake Havasu City, Ariz., and Laughlin, Nev.
   Other reports at 5 a.m. EDT:
